==English==

===Noun===
'''facebook'''  (''plural:'' '''facebooks''')

# A [[reference]] [[book]] made up of individuals' [[photographs]] and names. 
# An electronic directory that provides names and photographs of individuals, most commonly within academic institutions.  Common publishers of electronic facebooks include PhotoBooks, Inc., AboutFace Corporation, and Coffee Pond Productions.
# A [[college]] [[publication]] distributed at the start of the academic year by [[university]] [[administration]]s with the intention of helping [[students]] get to know each other better.
#:''The shipment of facebooks will be distributed to the freshmen during orientation and move-in-week.''

